  • public class TH_ISO14443_4_MIFARE_Plus_SL3
extends TH_ISO14443_4_MIFARE_Plus
    Class for ISO 14443-4 transponder Infineon MIFARE Plus in Security Level 3.
    This class supports only selected mode in Host-Mode

    Description:
    High-level class for easy-to-use Transponder specific communication. See ITagGroup for additional information.
    This class implements the communication with [0xC2] Reader commands.
    Detailed description about the command interface can be found in:
    - Product Datasheet for MIFARE Plus from NXP Semiconductors
    - System Manual SoftCrypto Functions from FEIG ELECTRONIC

    Note: Programmers should be familiar with the ISO 14443 standards.

    • Method Detail

      • resetAuthentication

        public int resetAuthentication()
                        throws FeException
        Reset Authent command
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        Security Level 3 Reset Authent.
        This method is realized with the Reader command [0xC2][0x78] and only applicable, if the Transponder is in selected mode.
        Detailed description about the command and the parameters can be found in:
        - Product Datasheet for MIFARE Plus from NXP Semiconductors
        - System Manual SoftCrypto Functions from FEIG ELECTRONIC
        The Transponder must be selected first with ITagGroup.tagSelect.

        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
